    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bindings stamped with designs by means of relatively large engraved blocks or plates that require a mechanical press; popular in the 15th and 16th centuries and revived in the 19th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Banden gestempeld met patronen door middel van tamelijk grote gegraveerde blokken of platen waarvoor een mechanische pers nodig is. Populair in de vijftiende en zestiende eeuw en opnieuw in de negentiende eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以大型刻版機器壓印的裝幀法；盛行於西元十五和十六世紀，並於西元十九世紀再度流行。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
